            <title>[CASSANDRA-5363] Missing files in debian /etc/cassandra/conf folder</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5363</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The standard debian installation puts;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cassandra-env.sh cassandra.yaml log4j-server.properties&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;into /etc/cassandra. However there seem to be additional files that might make sense there:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;commitlog_archiving.properties cassandra-rackdc.properties log4j-tools.properties cassandra-topology.properties&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(these are at least installed by the DSC rpm installer). So should those be added in debian or removed in rpms?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
